-- European Stocks Rise as Fed Prepared to Buy Debt; Fresnillo, ASML Advance
-- B y   W i l l   H a d f i e l d
-- 2010-10-13T07:06:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-13/european-stocks-rise-as-fed-prepared-to-buy-debt-fresnillo-asml-advance.html
European stocks advanced after the
U.S. Federal Reserve published minutes showing that policy
makers are prepared to buy more government debt.  The benchmark Stoxx Europe 600 Index gained 0.2 percent to
263.03 as of 8:05 a.m. in London. Fresnillo Plc and ASML Holding
NV climbed as the shares of Standard Chartered Plc retreated.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Will Hadfield at 
 whadfield@bloomberg.net  